[{"id":"FT539589","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"A painting of Napoleon is shown. It shows Napoleon as the emperor seated on a circular-backed throne with armrests adorned with ivory balls. In his right hand, he holds the sceptre of Charlemagne and in his left the hand of justice. On his head is a golden laurel wreath. He also wears an ermine hood under the great collar of the Legion d'honneur, a gold-embroidered satin tunic and an ermine-lined cloak decorated with gold prints. The coronation sword is in its scabbard and held up by a silk scarf. He wears white shoes embroidered in gold and resting on a cushion. The carpet under the throne displays an imperial eagle.\" height=\"312\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/bc6736ad3bd4971cd65041136839d0af/original.png\" width=\"200\" /></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:0.8em\">Giraudon/Art Resource</span></p>\n\n<p>The painting of Napoleon shown above portrays him as which of the following?</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<p>A chivalrous hero</p>","<p>A compassionate humanist</p>","<p>A competent bureaucrat</p>","<p>An imperial ruler</p>","<p>A ruthless military conqueror</p>"],"answer":2}]